sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2036018
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zhangyu Cheng
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: pRE, Cro and CII are all from bacteriaphage lambda.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This is Cro and CII tandom expression. CII expressed at the downtream of pRE can form a positive feedback to enhance Cro's expression to reach a ideal exppression level.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Signal Fil
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zhangyu Cheng
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: RFP and GFP are all standard parts from the Registry, while pRM are adopted from bacteriaphage lambda.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It is constructed to build a bi-stable system with RFP and GFP as reporters.
